You can only obtain deuterium from dense or rich ice asteroids found in special asteroid fields. You can find them all over the place but only around cold stars like class M or class D.
@p9You can only mine these asteroids with special ice mining lasers. They come in two varieties, a manual version and an automatic version.

The ice takes up a lot of space and I recommend having on-board deconstructors to break down the ice for you.

@p9Be wary of bandit attacks as they see miners as helpless targets. Bring some miniguns or flak to keep them at bay.

You can find better ice in the galactic region of Solitude, but it is a longer trip to sell your ice.

Good luck out there!

