@d0Yes, an active teleporter requires a vast amount of energy to keep running, but with careful signal logic you can bypass this.
With the setup I'm about to show you, stepping on the <color=#00ff00>teleporter</color> will turn on the teleporter and turn off your <color=#00ff00>shields</color>, then after you teleport away the <color=#00ff00>teleporter</color> will turn off and your <color=#00ff00>shields</color> will turn back on.
@p9 @d0Step 1: Setup a <color=#00ff00>motion sensor</color> to cover the teleporter area.
Step 2: Set the teleporter to <color=#00ff00>FOLLOW</color> that signal.
Step 3: <color=#ffffff>(Optional)</color> Set your ship's shields to <color=#00ff00>FOLLOW</color> that signal with the <color=#00ff00>INVERTED</color><color=#ffffff>(i)</color> box checked.
Now your teleporter will only be active when you are actually using it, saving a lot of fuel.

Project Eden was formed alongside Operation Phoenix by the trillionaire Dr. Smith. Smith discovered a second set of coordinates in the alien artifacts found buried on Earth and believed it led to a paradise.
Using her wealth and influence, she convinced the United Council of Humanity to let her build her own fleet of jump capable ships to establish a new home for Humanity in the Andromeda galaxy. Things didn't exactly go as planned.
@p9At first everything was good. We arrived in Andromeda along with a UCH military escort. The alien hyperspace drives burned out but that wasn't completely unexpected. Very soon after however, we encountered a hostile alien species known as the Zirax. Not just any Zirax. Zirax from House Abyssal. They opened fire on our fleet and Dr Smith used her ship to give the rest of the fleet time to escape.
@p9Her ship was destroyed saving the rest of the fleet, but we did detect several escape pods being launched before the hyperspace drive overloaded. Nobody knows if she survived. 
@p9Now everyone is scattered throughout Andromeda. House Abyssal has placed a bounty on the heads of any Terran to be delivered to them alive. They have been getting the other houses to attack us on sight so we have to keep moving.
Some of the survivors have established small colonies, others continue to work on research vessels such as these. And some, well, let's just say that some of us don't forgive easily.

@q0Welcome, you must be new here!
I am the lead researcher! My job here is to help manage the overall research and direct people to new locations to discover.
To my left and right are the Schematic Computer and Research Computer.
You can use them to unlock new schematics, upgrade your warp drive range, or turn in data chips or data pads.
Please take a moment to look them over before moving on.
@p9When you are finished making your introductions, come speak with me again and I will answer any other questions you may have.

