@d0Dear {Player.Name}, I hope this message finds you well over in {Player.PlayfieldName}.
Don't be surprised to learn I know where you are. I have been keeping a close eye on you. You might call me an admirer of sorts.
I write to you today with an opportunity for both of us. A win-win as you Terrans are so fond of saying.
I have seen that you are an individual of questionable morals, and I have a problem that needs someone who isn't afraid to get their hands dirty.
@p9 @d0Several colonist freighters have fallen behind on paying their insurance dues and are no longer insured. I need you to pay one of them a visit and give them a gentle reminder to renew their insurance policy before something bad happens to them. I think once the news spreads the others will be more than eager to pay up.
@p9 @d0It's important that you only disable their ship, not destroy it. Try to avoid targeting their cores or generators as dead clients can't pay their dues and other freighter captains won't trust you for a period of time.
